---
import DocLayout from "../../../components/DocLayout.astro";

const title = "Core Primitives - AgentInterface Documentation";
const description = "Learn about the core primitives of the AgentInterface protocol.";
---

<DocLayout 
	title={title}
	description={description}
	canonicalUrl="https://agentinterface.dev/docs/primitives"
	keywords="agentinterface primitives, core concepts, protocol"
>
	<h1 class="mb-8 text-4xl font-bold">Core Primitives</h1>
	
	<div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
		<p class="text-xl mb-8">
			AgentInterface is built on a set of core primitives that define how agents communicate with UI renderers.
		</p>
		
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Protocol</h2>
		<p>
			The AgentInterface Protocol defines the structure and format of messages exchanged between agents and UI renderers.
			It ensures consistency across different implementations and platforms.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-4">
			<a href="/docs/primitives/protocol" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">
				Learn more about the Protocol &rarr;
			</a>
		</p>
		
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Component</h2>
		<p>
			Components are the building blocks of the UI. They represent different types of UI elements that agents can use to
			communicate with users, such as text, images, buttons, and more.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-4">
			<a href="/docs/primitives/component" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">
				Learn more about Components &rarr;
			</a>
		</p>
		
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Response</h2>
		<p>
			A Response is a container for components. It represents a complete message from an agent to a user, containing
			one or more components.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-4">
			<a href="/docs/primitives/response" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">
				Learn more about Responses &rarr;
			</a>
		</p>
		
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Action</h2>
		<p>
			Actions define interactive behaviors that components can trigger. They allow users to interact with the UI and
			provide feedback to the agent.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-4">
			<a href="/docs/primitives/action" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">
				Learn more about Actions &rarr;
			</a>
		</p>
		
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Renderer</h2>
		<p>
			Renderers transform AgentInterface responses into actual UI components for different frameworks and platforms.
			They handle the rendering of components and the execution of actions.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-4">
			<a href="/docs/primitives/renderer" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">
				Learn more about Renderers &rarr;
			</a>
		</p>
	</div>
</DocLayout>